104: Conserved cysteine from V gene — germline encoded.

105–107: V gene contribution — mostly germline, sometimes trimmed.

108–111: V-D junction — heavily influenced by N-insertions (TdT) and palindromic nucleotides (P-nucleotides). This is the first main region of non-templated diversity.

112–115: D gene segment — germline-derived.

116–117: D-J junction — again dominated by N-insertions; second main source of non-templated diversity.

118: Conserved phenylalanine (F), tryptophan (W), or tyrosine (Y) from J gene — germline encoded.

✅ Key takeaway:

Non-templated indels are concentrated at junctions: 108–111 and 116–117.

Germline sequences dominate the ends (104–107 V, 112–115 D, 118 J).


